data.name: label2.Text
data.value: The American continent was discovered by the Italian sailor Christopher Columbus in 1492, but it was Amerigo Vespucci, who claimed it was the "New World" because Columbus thought it was the Indian island. After the discovery of the continent, the Spaniards, the Portuguese, the French and the British were the landowners of the Europeans. The 13 states in which the British formed colonies and now include Boston, New York, Philadelphia and Washington are the basis of the US. The British began to fight for the independence of the British colony in the United States when the British received heavy taxes from the colonies and increased their response to the day by day. The American Declaration of Independence was proclaimed by the American Declaration of Independence, published by George Washington on 4 July 1776. In this declaration, which declares the establishment of the US to the whole world, it has been reported that the American people will establish a new government and the form of government will be democracy. With the Paris Treaty of 1783, the United Kingdom adopted the independence of the United States, and the United States was officially established in 1787.
